video.title: ROUTINE CARDIAC CATHETERIZATION BENEFITS SOME WOMEN WITH HEART DISEASE MORE THAN OTHERS
video.description: Heart disease is the number one killer of women each year in the United States.  Cardiac catheterization is a routine procedure that allows doctors to find potential blockages in coronary arteries in order to help prevent new heart attacks and even death.  A recent study finds that high risk women, who do have a heart attack, benefit from this procedure just as much as men.  But for some women the procedure may not always be the best option.
